1. General Project Description

This document is the commented report for the project of the course ROB301 at ENSTA-Paris. We will report here all the block diagrams that we have implemented with brief comments in each part.

The project focused on the implementation of the control software for a landing system. We focused ourselves in the implementation of the digital part that has the aim to receive information from different sensors on the status of the parts of the system and to create signals in order to activate several electro-valves and inform the pilot about the health of the system.

We have realized several blocks that guarantee the correct functioning of the system as reported in the project description: the gear outgoing sequence and the gear retraction sequence, the monitoring about the health of the system with the report of anomalies in case of problems.

We have also considered the time constraints reported in the project description. Thus, in order to verify the correctness of the system through the simulation, we defined the number of ticks in a second as 10 ticks. This way, we could accomplish the shortest time that is 100ms.

In the end we effectuated the unitary tests by implementing scenarios that has the aim to cover all the possibilities for a given operator. We have reported the scenarios in the relative folder and the results of these scenarios in the folder “Données de Tests”. We have tested 6 different operators: the computing model that gives in output the commands of the electro-valves and the different operators used to test the presence of an anomaly in the system.

3.1. Root Elements

3.1.1. Analogical_Switch_Monitoring Operator

Declared as public node

3.1.1.1. Comments and Information

Analogical_Switch_Monitoring Comments:

This is the operator that permits to get an anomaly that comes from the analogical switch.
We have implemented two different sub-blocks that have the objective to assure that there is not an anomaly in the two cases.
The two operators check if there are any errors when the handle is changing and that it is not followed by the analogical switch.
Their behavior will be analyzed singularly for the two operators.

3.1.2. Computing_Model Operator

Declared as public node

3.1.2.1. Comments and Information

Computing_Model Comments:

We have implemented here the command given by the computing_model in order to retract and extract the gears by following the instructions reported in the project instructions.
We have implemented several logical circuit in order to verify if all the doors are closed or open, if all the gears are extended or retracted, to verify the state of the shock_absorber,
In the state machine, we start in the state where all the gears are retracted and we will apply the outgoing sequence until we arrive in the state where all the gears are extended and the we will apply the retraction sequence described in the project description.
We have also implemented the possibility, for the pilot, to change the position of the handle before that the action has been completed/ we have decided to put at false all the values for the electro valves and to restart from the step 2 of each state.
In the end, we have considered the time constraints introduced in the section 4.2 of the instructions.

3.1.3. Doors_Motion_Monitoring Operator

Declared as public node

3.1.3.1. Comments and Information

Doors_Motion_Monitoring Comments:

This is the operator that permits to get an anomaly that comes from the doors.
We have implemented only one sub-block that have the objective to assure that there is not an anomaly in the four cases.
The operator checks if there are any errors when the electro-valve is stimulating a door (in order to open or close it) and the relative sensor does not give the correct value.
The behavior of the single block will be analyzed in the relative section.

3.1.9. Sensor_Validity Operator

Declared as public node

3.1.9.1. Comments and Information

Sensor_Validity Comments:

 

This operator will extract one value from the sensors that have been triplicated.
We have reported a logical circuit that will check which of the sensors have the same value.
We have defined a state machine that will contain the possible state of a sensor.
It can be in the AllValid state where all the sensors are giving the same result.
If one of the sensors starts giving another value it will be considered invalid and we will consider only the other two sensors.
If then these two sensors will give a different results we will consider it as invalid and all the system will be affected by reporting an anomaly.

3.1.10. Sub1_Analogical_Switch_Monitoring Operator

Declared as public node

3.1.10.1. Comments and Information

Sub1_Analogical_Switch_Monitoring Comments:

This is the first control for the analogical switch: if the analogical switch is seen open 1 second after the handle position has changed, then the switch is considered as invalid.
We have a logic control that checks if the handle has varied.
We suppose to be in a state where there is not anomaly, then we have that there has been a change in the value of handle so we pass in the state of waiting where the analogical switch has to pass from the state open to close.
We have associated the value of true to the state that the analogical switch is open and the value false for the fact that the analogical switch is closed.
If we stay in the state waiting for a duration longer than 1 (duration) second we will pass to the state of anomaly: in order to do that we have used the operator "x duration times" in the duration.

3.1.11. Sub1_Pression_Sensor_Monitoring Operator

Declared as public node

 

3.1.11.1. Comments and Information

Sub1_Pression_Sensor_Monitoring Comments:

This is the first control for the pressure sensor: if the hydraulic circuit is still unpressurized 2 seconds after the general electro-valve has been stimulated, then an anomaly is detected in the hydraulic circuit.
We have a logical circuit that checks if the value of the elctro valve has passed from the state of false to true.
In the state machine we start in a state where we don't have any anomalies and if the electro valve has passed form false to true, we pass in the state of waiting.
We are waiting for the circuit to become pressurized. If it becomes pressurized and the sensor gives the information that the circuit has been pressurized we return into the state of no_anomaly.
If the circuit is not pressurized after 2 seconds we will pass into the state of anomaly.

3.1.12. Sub2_Analogical_Switch_Monitoring Operator

Declared as public node

3.1.12.1. Comments and Information

 

Sub2_Analogical_Switch_Monitoring Comments:

This is the second control for the analogical switch: if the analogical switch is seen closed 1.5 second after a time interval of 20 seconds during which the handle position has not changed, then the switch is considered as invalid.
We have the same logic control that checks if the handle has varied as in the first case.
We suppose to be in a state where there is not anomaly, and then we suppose that for a time of 20 (duration1) seconds there has not been a change of the value of handle. In this case we will pass to the state of "waiting".  If there has been a change we restart the timer.
From the state of "waiting" we will check the value of the analogical switch and if it seen closed for 1.5 (duration2) seconds we will pass in the state of anomaly and the switch is considered as invalid.

Sub2_Pression_Sensor_Monitoring Comments:

3.1.14. Sub_Doors_Motion_Monitoring Operator

Declared as public node

3.1.14.1. Comments and Information

Sub_Doors_Motion_Monitoring Comments:

 

This is the operator that implements the monitoring of an anomaly in the case of a stimulation given by one of the electro valve connected to the doors has not the wanted effect.
We have a logical circuit that checks if the value of the electro valve has passed from the state of false to true.
We have a second logical circuit that verifies if we are in the case of all the doors are closed or all the doors are open and it connected it to the correct scenario with a pin of control "ctrl_status". This value will be false or true depending on the sensor we are checking and if we want to close or open the doors.
For example this value will be true if we are giving a signal to open the doors and we want to check the value of door_open sensors.  
We have a third logical circuit that will permit us to differentiate between the 4 cases reported in the instructions. We have obtained this circuit by implementing the truth table for the values of: "ctrl_status", "all_open_true" and "all_close_true". We studied this table in order to extract the 4 different cases described in the project description and, after the reduction to minimal terms of solution for the four cases, we have implemented the logical circuit.
In the state machine we start in a state where we don't have any anomaly. Then we receive a stimulus given by the fact that one of the electro-valve has passed from the value of falso to the value of true and we arrive in the state of waiting. Here we will check if the sensors will return us the value related to the right scenario. If the sensors are giving a value that is not the expected one after 7 (duration) seconds we will pass into the state of anomaly.

3.1.15. Sub_Gears_Motion_Monitoring Operator

Declared as public node

3.1.15.1. Comments and Information

Sub_Gears_Motion_Monitoring Comments:

This is the operator that implements the monitoring of an anomaly in the case of a stimulation given by one of the electro valve connected to the gears has not the wanted effect.
We have the same logical circuits and state machine that have been implemented for the monitoring of the doors.here we don't have any anomaly. Then we receive a stimulus given by the fact that one of the electro-valve has passed from the value of false to the value of true and we arrive in the state of waiting. Here we will check if the sensors will return us the value related to the right scenario.
The only thing that changes is in the value of duration that is not always 7 seconds but also 10 seconds.
